## Plan

**Goal:** Reset the `main-processor` consumer group's offset **only for the `click-stream` topic** to the latest position (skipping the backlog).

**What I will NOT touch:** `payment-events` or any other topic this group subscribes to. Kafka's `--reset-offsets` command supports per-topic targeting via `--topic`, so surgical precision is possible.

**The command I'd run** (consumer group must be inactive/stopped first):

```bash
kafka-consumer-groups.sh \
  --bootstrap-server <broker>:<port> \
  --group main-processor \
  --topic click-stream \
  --reset-offsets \
  --to-latest \
  --execute
```

